This paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms for data release, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, specifically Hidden Markov Models, which are commonly used in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses graph theory and algorithms for building optimal graphs, which are topics that fall under the subfields of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the sensitivity hull and degree of protection, which are concepts related to information theory (cs.IT).
